= 8.1 Structural Organization of the Brain

- The *central nervous system (CNS)* (中枢神经系统) consists of the brain and spinal cord
- The brain contains an enormous number of *association neurons* (联络神经元) and *neuroglia* (神经胶质细胞)
- The CNS receives input from *sensory neurons* (感觉神经元) and directs *motor neurons* (运动神经元) that innervate muscles and glands
- The brain is capable of *learning* (学习) and *memory* (记忆), most highly developed in humans
- *Perceptions* (感知), learning, memory, emotions (情绪), and logical thinking (逻辑思维) are all accomplished by the brain

#figure(
  image(images.at("8-1").path, width: 50%),
)

== Embryonic Development of the CNS

- The CNS develops from embryonic *ectoderm* (外胚层)
- The *neural tube* (神经管) forms by day 20 after conception when a neural groove deepens and fuses
- The *neural crest* (神经嵴) forms between the neural tube and surface ectoderm
- The neural tube becomes the central nervous system
- The neural crest becomes ganglia (神经节) of the peripheral nervous system

#figure(
  image(images.at("8-2").path, width: 50%),
)

== Brain Regions and Development

- By the fourth week, three brain regions form:
  - *Forebrain* (*prosencephalon*, 前脑)
  - *Midbrain* (*mesencephalon*, 中脑)
  - *Hindbrain* (*rhombencephalon*, 后脑)
- By the fifth week, five regions develop:
  - *Telencephalon* (端脑) - from forebrain
  - *Diencephalon* (间脑) - from forebrain
  - *Mesencephalon* (中脑) - unchanged
  - *Metencephalon* (后脑) - from hindbrain
  - *Myelencephalon* (髓脑) - from hindbrain

#figure(
  image(images.at("8-3").path, width: 50%),
)

- The *telencephalon* grows disproportionately in humans, forming the two enormous *cerebral hemispheres* (大脑半球) that cover other brain regions
- The brain begins as a hollow tube and remains hollow as regions form
- The cavities are called *ventricles* (脑室), filled with *cerebrospinal fluid (CSF)* (脑脊液)
- The spinal cord cavity is the *central canal* (中央管)

#figure(
  image(images.at("8-4").path, width: 50%),
)

== Gray and White Matter Organization

- *Gray matter* (灰质) contains neuron cell bodies and dendrites, found in:
  - The *cortex* (皮层) - surface layer of the brain
  - *Nuclei* (核团) - deeper aggregations within the brain
- *White matter* (白质) consists of *axon tracts* (轴突束) with myelin sheaths (髓鞘) producing white color
- White matter underlies the cortex and surrounds the nuclei
- The adult brain contains approximately 100 billion (#ce("10^11")) neurons
- The brain weighs approximately 1.5 kg (3-3.5 lb)
- The brain receives about 15% of total blood flow per minute due to high metabolic requirements

== Neurogenesis in the Adult Brain

- Adult mammalian brains, including humans, contain *neural stem cells* (神经干细胞) that can develop into neurons and glial cells
- *Neurogenesis* (神经发生) - formation of new neurons from neural stem cells - occurs in two locations:
  - *Subventricular zone* (室下区) - adjacent to ependymal cells lining the lateral ventricles
    - Newborn neurons migrate to *olfactory bulbs* (嗅球)
    - Enhanced by olfactory learning
  - *Subgranular zone* (颗粒下区) within the *hippocampus* (海马)
    - Newly formed neurons may aid hippocampus-dependent learning

= 8.2 Cerebrum

- The *cerebrum* (大脑) is the only structure of the telencephalon
- Largest portion of the brain, accounting for about 80% of its mass
- Primarily responsible for higher mental functions
- Consists of right and left *cerebral hemispheres* (大脑半球)
- The hemispheres are connected by the *corpus callosum* (胼胝体), a major fiber tract

#figure(
  image(images.at("8-5").path, width: 50%),
)

== Cerebral Cortex Structure

- The cerebrum consists of an outer *cerebral cortex* (大脑皮层) of 2-4 mm gray matter and underlying white matter
- The cortex is characterized by numerous folds and grooves called *convolutions* (脑回)
- Elevated folds are *gyri* (脑回, singular: gyrus)
- Depressed grooves are *sulci* (脑沟, singular: sulcus)
- Deep sulci are called *fissures* (裂)

== Cerebral Lobes

- Each hemisphere is subdivided by deep sulci into five lobes:
  - *Frontal lobe* (额叶) - visible from surface
  - *Parietal lobe* (顶叶) - visible from surface
  - *Temporal lobe* (颞叶) - visible from surface
  - *Occipital lobe* (枕叶) - visible from surface
  - *Insula* (脑岛) - deep lobe covered by portions of frontal, parietal, and temporal lobes

#figure(
  image(images.at("8-6").path, width: 50%),
)

#figure(
  image(images.at("table-8-1").path, width: 70%),
)

== Motor and Sensory Areas

- The *precentral gyrus* (中央前回) of the frontal lobe contains the *primary motor cortex* (初级运动皮层)
  - Controls voluntary movements of skeletal muscles
  - Exhibits *somatotopic organization* (体感定位组织) - body representation in specific cortical areas
  - Larger cortical areas devoted to body parts requiring fine motor control (hands, face)
- The *postcentral gyrus* (中央后回) of the parietal lobe contains the *primary somatosensory cortex* (初级躯体感觉皮层)
  - Receives sensory information from body
  - Also shows somatotopic organization
  - Larger areas for sensitive body parts (lips, fingertips)
- The *motor homunculus* (运动小人) and *sensory homunculus* (感觉小人) show distorted body representations reflecting cortical space allocation

